						               													<description>Memoir '44: Campaign Book Volume 2, the second hardcover supplement for the Memoir '44 game system, contains 46 new scenarios and builds upon the campaign rules introduced in Campaign Book Volume 1 to let players experience scenarios in succession, with the outcome of each battle impacting the next.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These 46 scenarios are grouped into eleven different campaigns, with two set in the Pacific Theater &amp;ndash; &amp;quot;Island Hoppers&amp;quot;, a Grand Campaign covering the progressive re-conquest of the Pacific by the Allied forces following the attack on Pearl Harbor, and &amp;quot;Bicycle Blitzkrieg&amp;quot;, the Japanese invasion of Malaya in 1941-1942 &amp;ndash; and the first Breakthrough campaign for Memoir '44: &amp;quot;Breakthrough Normandy&amp;quot;, covering the Allied offensive in Normandy from D-Day through August 1944.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two other campaigns &amp;ndash; &amp;quot;Fall of Poland&amp;quot;, depicting the desperate resistance of Polish forces against the German Blitzkrieg of September 1939, and &amp;quot;Air Aces&amp;quot;, a campaign following the exploits of famous air aces throughout World War II &amp;ndash; round up the Theaters of Operations covered in the book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Memoir '44: Campaign Book Volume 2 comes with a punchboard containing fifty game tokens and requires the Memoir '44 base game as well as theater-specific expansions for some of the campaigns, specifically Memoir '44: Pacific Theater, Memoir '44: Air Pack, Memoir '44: Terrain Pack and Memoir '44: Breakthrough.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
